<dl id="s14040u"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="us14" href="#s14040u">Oxen of the Sun: </a><a href="../../ff/unbs/s14all.htm#s14040u">sector 40(u)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> then only &hellip; when</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Some men of fortune and universal benevolence propose the proper objects; the wants and the merits of the petitioners are canvassed by the people; neither passion nor pity find a place in the cool discussion; and charity is <mark>then only exerted when</mark> it has received the approbation of reason. <small> Oliver Goldsmith, <a name="OGCW" href="/udra/udex.htm#ogcw"><cite title="source">Complete Works</cite></a> (n.d), <i>Citizen of the World</i>, p 440</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
